---
openclaw:
  workspace_path: "~/.openclaw/workspaces"
  default_agent: "developer"

plugin_defaults:
  author_name: "Your Name"
  author_email: "your.email@example.com"

deployment:
  openclaw_plugins_dir: "~/.openclaw/plugins"
  claude_code_plugins_dir: "~/.claude/plugins"

testing:
  auto_validate: true
  run_verification: true

gateways:
  - name: local
    host: 127.0.0.1
    gateway_port: 18789

  - name: home-mac
    host: 192.168.1.100
    gateway_port: 18789
    ssh_port: 22
    ssh_user: haowu
    ssh_key: ~/.ssh/id_ed25519
    gateway_token_env: HOME_MAC_GW_TOKEN
    tags: [home, dev]

  - name: cloud-server
    host: 10.0.0.5
    gateway_port: 18789
    ssh_port: 22
    ssh_user: root
    gateway_token_env: CLOUD_GW_TOKEN
    tags: [cloud, production]
---

# OpenClaw-Dev Local Configuration

This file contains local configuration for the openclaw-dev plugin. Copy this to `.claude/openclaw-dev.local.md` and customize for your environment.

## Configuration Fields

### openclaw.workspace_path
Path to OpenClaw workspaces directory. Used when deploying skills to agent workspaces.

Default: `~/.openclaw/workspaces`

### openclaw.default_agent
Default agent ID to use when creating skills. Will be prompted if not set.

Example: `developer`, `analyst`, `researcher`

### plugin_defaults.author_name
Your name to use in plugin.json manifests by default.

### plugin_defaults.author_email
Your email to use in plugin.json manifests by default.

### deployment.openclaw_plugins_dir
Where to deploy plugins for OpenClaw use.

Default: `~/.openclaw/plugins`

### deployment.claude_code_plugins_dir
Where to deploy plugins for Claude Code use.

Default: `~/.claude/plugins`

### testing.auto_validate
Automatically run validation after creating plugins/skills/agents.

Default: `true`

### testing.run_verification
Run verification scripts after deployment.

Default: `true`

## Gateways Configuration

Multi-Gateway management for `/diagnose`, `/openclaw-status`, `/fleet-ssh`.

### gateways[].name
Gateway alias, used as command argument (e.g., `/diagnose home-mac`).

### gateways[].host
IP address, hostname, Tailscale MagicDNS name, or SSH config alias.

### gateways[].gateway_port
OpenClaw Gateway port. Default: `18789`

### gateways[].ssh_port
SSH daemon port for remote connections. Default: `22`

### gateways[].ssh_user
SSH username for remote gateways. Required for non-local gateways.

### gateways[].ssh_key
Path to SSH private key. Default: system default.

### gateways[].gateway_token_env
Environment variable name containing the Gateway auth token. Never store tokens directly — use env vars.

### gateways[].tags
Optional tags for future grouping support (e.g., `[cloud, production]`).

## Usage

This configuration is read by openclaw-dev commands:
- `/scaffold-plugin` - Uses plugin_defaults for author info
- `/create-skill` - Uses openclaw.workspace_path and default_agent
- `/deploy-skill` - Uses deployment paths
- `/validate-plugin` - Uses testing.auto_validate setting
- `/diagnose` - Uses gateways for remote diagnosis
- `/openclaw-status` - Uses gateways for remote status queries
- `/fleet-ssh` - Uses gateways for interactive SSH connections

## Notes

- This file should be in `.gitignore` (contains local paths)
- Settings are optional - commands will prompt if not configured
- Paths support tilde expansion (`~` for home directory)
- YAML frontmatter format for easy parsing
